sql:
SELECT debug_id, addr_diff
FROM debug_info
WHERE debug_type = 'DBG_ADVANCE_PC';

external_knowledge:
Code item ID 1 refers to the top-level code item in the hierarchical structure; 
The 'level' in the context of this query represents the depth of the debug entry in the hierarchical structure; 
The 'cumulative address difference' and 'cumulative line difference' refer to the running totals of the addr_diff and line_diff values, respectively, for each code item, ordered by the level of the debug entries.

sql:
SELECT code
FROM code_items
WHERE class_name = 'MyClass';

SELECT code
FROM code_items
WHERE code_item_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
; Code items 0 and 1 refer to the specific IDs of the code snippets in the code items table; 
; The average line difference is calculated for each debug type separately; 
; Debug types with an average line difference less than or equal to 0 are excluded from the results.

'local variable declarations' refers to debug_type 'DBG_START_LOCAL' and 'DBG_START_LOCAL_EXTENDED' ; 
'debug_type' DBG_START_LOCAL and DBG_START_LOCAL_EXTENDED are types of debug information in the debug_info table ; 
'first code item' refers to code_item_id = 1.
